com.hazelcast.spi.impl.proxyservice.impl

Class ProxyRegistry

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.hazelcast.spi.impl.proxyservice.impl.ProxyRegistry

  • public final class ProxyRegistry
extends Object
    A ProxyRegistry contains all proxies for a given service. For example, it contains all proxies for the IMap.

        public DistributedObject getOrCreateProxy(String name,

        Parameters:

        publishEvent - true if a DistributedObjectEvent should be fired.

        The DistributedObject instance.

      • getOrCreateProxyFuture

        public DistributedObjectFuture getOrCreateProxyFuture(String name,
                                                      boolean publishEvent,
                                                      boolean initialize)
        Retrieves a DistributedObjectFuture or creates it if it is not available. If initialize is false and DistributedObject implements InitializingObject, InitializingObject.initialize() will be called before DistributedObjectFuture.get() returns.
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the DistributedObject proxy object to retrieve or create.
        publishEvent - true if a DistributedObjectEvent should be fired.
        initialize - true if the DistributedObject proxy object should be initialized.
